Package io.github.bluelhf.anemone

Class Anemones

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.bluelhf.anemone.Anemones
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.bukkit.event.Listener
    public class Anemones
extends Object
implements org.bukkit.event.Listener
    Anemones is a handler singleton for Anemone subclasses. To use Anemones, it must first be initialised with init(Plugin).

      • init

        public static void init​(org.bukkit.plugin.Plugin host)
        Initialises Anemones using the given plugin. If Anemones is already initialised, the plugin will be added to the hosts deque of Anemones. Anemones will only disable when the hosts queue is empty.
        Parameters:
        host - The plugin to initialise Anemones with

      • register

        public static void register​(Anemone anemone)
        Registers a new subclass of Anemone. Useful if your Anemone subclass takes constructor parameters.
        Parameters:
        anemone - The subclass of Anemone to register
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If Anemones isn't initialised
        See Also:
        register(Class)

      • unregister

        public static void unregister​(Class<? extends Anemone> anemoneClass)

        Parameters:
